NFSv4 export administration.

GrainFS exports each S3 bucket as an independent NFSv4 mount point.
Use 'grainfs nfs export add <bucket>' to register a bucket as an NFS export.

Usage:
  grainfs nfs [command]

Available Commands:
  debug       Diagnose an NFS bucket export
  export      Manage NFSv4 export registrations

Flags:
      --endpoint string    admin Unix socket path (required, e.g. ./tmp/admin.sock)
  -h, --help               help for nfs
      --timeout duration   admin command timeout (e.g. 30s, 5m); unset = 30s default; 0 = uncapped (for long follow loops)

Global Flags:
      --log-level string   log level: debug, info, warn, error (default "info")

Use "grainfs nfs [command] --help" for more information about a command.
